This paper deals with natural language processing and machine translation, which are core topics in the computer science subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with structured query languages and databases, which are topics in database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different neural machine translation models, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
